comment:
* Base dialog result data.
 *
 * Returned for simple use cases like cancellation. Can also be subclassed when more information
 * is needed, e.g. {@link UserSelectionDialogResult}.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: EXTRA_BASE_RESULT
variables.comment:
* The intent extra key for the {@code BaseDialogResult} object when the credential
     * selector activity finishes.

variables.name: RESULT_CODE_CANCELED_AND_LAUNCHED_SETTINGS
variables.comment:
* The UI was stopped since the user has chosen to navigate to the Settings UI to reconfigure
     * their providers.

variables.name: RESULT_CODE_DIALOG_COMPLETE_WITH_SELECTION
variables.comment:
* User made a selection and the dialog finished. The user selection result is in the
     * {@code resultData}.

variables.name: RESULT_CODE_DATA_PARSING_FAILURE
variables.comment: * The UI was canceled because it failed to parse the incoming data.

methods.name: public static BaseDialogResult fromResultData(@NonNull Bundle resultData)
methods.comment: Parses and returns a BaseDialogResult from the given resultData.

methods.name: public static void addToBundle(@NonNull BaseDialogResult result, @NonNull Bundle bundle)
methods.comment:
* Used for the UX to construct the {@code resultData Bundle} to send via the {@code
     * ResultReceiver}.

methods.name: public IBinder getRequestToken()
methods.comment:
* Returns the unique identifier for the request that launched the operation.
     *
     * @deprecated do not use

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)

methodNames: public static BaseDialogResult fromResultData(@NonNull Bundle resultData)
public static void addToBundle(@NonNull BaseDialogResult result, @NonNull Bundle bundle)
public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
